channel.title: [DELTA]::Teleto Command[DELTA]
channel.description:
Ok, I have a DELTA server, and bluur's client, but I can not find out where my ::teleto command is. I checked in client.java on both, client and server side. I can't seem to find the code, but the command works for admins+ so It must be coded somewhere? I want to edit this code so I can make it teleport me to a different height, because right now, it only teleports me to absX and absY. I want it to teleport me to absX absY height. Can someone tell me where this command is located? I can't find it anywhere. [I DID DO CTRL+F AND SEARCH "TELETO" IT STILL DID NOT FIND ANYTHING IN CLIENT.JAVA ON CLIENT, OR SERVER SIDE.]
I mean to teleport to a coordinate! ATM I can only do like, [code]::teleto 3000 3001[/code] that will teleport me to [code] absX: 3000 and absY: 3001 [/code] on the world map!
I want it to teleport me to absX absY and Height! for example, if I wanted to teleport to the 2nd floor of the lumbridge castle, I type [code] ::teleto absXCoord absYCoord HEIGHTLEVEL [/code]
I want to add in the heightlevel to the code, but I do not know where the code is. I am trying to break this down as much as i can..
[size=36pt]I already Have ::xteleto and ::xteletome[/size]
